$$\overrightarrow p  = 3\widehat i - \widehat j + 2\widehat k$$ &amp; $$\overrightarrow Q   = \widehat i + 2\widehat j - 4\widehat k$$<br><br>$${\overrightarrow v _{PR}} = (4, - 1,2)$$ &amp; $${\overrightarrow v _{QS}} = ( - 2,1, - 2)$$<br><br><img src="https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kooc538c/9ec0045c-b98f-40e4-a79f-9bf1bc9e4629/5016bdc0-b4b5-11eb-8621-259cd7dab099/file-1kooc538d.jpg" style="max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;" loading="lazy" alt="JEE Main 2021 (Online) 16th March Morning Shift Mathematics - 3D Geometry Question 266 English Explanation"><br><br>$${L_{PR}}:\overrightarrow r  = (3\widehat i - \widehat j + 2\widehat k) + \lambda (4, - 1,2)$$<br><br>$${L_{QS}}:\overrightarrow r  = (\widehat i + 2\widehat j - 4\widehat k) + \mu ( - 2,1, - 2)$$
