$$f'(x)\left\{ {\matrix{
   { - 4{x^2} + 4x + 3} &amp; {x &gt; 0}  \cr 
   {3{e^x}(1 + x)} &amp; {x \le 0}  \cr 

 } } \right.$$<br><br><img src="https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1krutwtxn/b16e8938-c778-41fa-a6b2-195f3cc75a8c/28cab5b0-f3ac-11eb-a605-b34dacb82f1b/file-1krutwtxo.png" style="max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;" loading="lazy" alt="JEE Main 2021 (Online) 22th July Evening Shift Mathematics - Application of Derivatives Question 114 English Explanation"><br>For x &gt; 0, $$f'(x) =  - 4{x^2} + 4x + 3$$<br><br>f(x) is increasing in $$\left( { - {1 \over 2},{3 \over 2}} \right)$$<br><br>For x $$\le$$ 0, f'(x) = 3e<sup>x</sup>(1 + x)<br><br>f'(x) &gt; 0 $$\forall$$ x $$\in$$($$-$$1, 0)<br><br>$$\Rightarrow$$ f(x) is increasing in ($$-$$1, 0)<br><br>So, in complete domain, f(x) is increasing in $$\left( { - 1,{3 \over 2}} \right)$$

